Candid Kid Covid Talk: What is COVID? What Symptoms/Signs are we seeking in children due to this pandemic and what can we do to help?

Join St. Luke's Behavioral Health School-based team for the series "The NEW Back to School" online events.
Sessions will be held on Tuesdays in September beginning on September 8th (TONIGHT) from 6 to 7 pm.

The first session is "Candid Kid COVID Talk: What is COVID? What symptoms/signs are we seeing in children due to this pandemic and what can we do to help?" Psychiatric Physician's Assistant, Amy Pulcini and moderator Jody McCloud Missmer will help to provide answers to these questions and much more.

To register for this live event, please click on the link below.

https://go.activecalendar.com/sluhn/event/the-new-back-to-school-online-event-series/

Each session will be recorded to view at a later date and registration is needed to access the playback.
#yoursalisbury

post_text:
Vaping is a serious challenge for today's youth. If you or someone you know is addicted to vaping or other unhealthy behaviors, reach out to your school counselor.

Nicotine comes from the tobacco plant, and it's found in ALL tobacco products, including cigarettes, chew, hookah and vape pods. No matter what form it's in, nicotine is the substance that gets you hooked! Don't be fooled ‚Äî vaping products contain addictive nicotine.

Tobacco and vape companies will do anything to get you hooked on nicotine. By keeping you craving more, these companies know they'll have customers for life. Teens who start with vaping are four times more likely to smoke cigarettes or use other forms of tobacco, and almost 90% of adults who use nicotine today started as teens. Don't get tricked!

#YourSalisbury

post_text:
LCTI will operate on the same hybrid schedule as SHS. Therefore, please note:

1. Student will attend LCTI on the same days they attend their in-person classes at SHS.
2. On the days that SHS students will not be in physical attendance at SHS or LCTI, there will be online learning taking place for both programs.
3. Students attending the Academic Center or CAP (full-day programs) will be provided online instruction for the off-site days but will attend LCTI all day on their in-person learning days (determined by last name).
4. All SHS students who participate in VAST can participate in LCTI programming on the days determined by their last names.

post_text: WSE Staff thanks the WSE PTA for all of their support. They have been beside us during some very difficult times. post_text:
A little Q&A with Salisbury Senior Wyatt Magee

What is your full name?
Wyatt Hunter Magee

What are your hobbies?
Playing video games

If you have pets, list what kind and names.
I have two dogs (Riley and Yogi) and four cats (Smokey, Ninja, Luna and Loki).

How would your friends describe you?
Funny, easy to talk to and helpful.

What is your favorite subject?
Math

Who is your favorite teacher?
I have several but if I have to pick one it would be Mr. Hahn.

What is your favorite movie?
Guardians of the Galaxy

Who is your role model and why?
Mr. Claude Kohl because I hope to have a similar career path in criminal justice. He has also been a great mentor and has given great advice.

What‚Äôs next after graduation?
I plan to attend LCCC for criminal justice and then transfer to a four-year college to pursue a bachelor‚Äôs degree in Criminal Justice.

#yoursalisbury

A little Q&A with Salisbury Senior Michael Acosta Jung

What is your full name?
Michael Acosta Jung

What are your hobbies?
Playing video games

How would your friends describe you?
Quiet

What is your favorite subject?
English

Who is your favorite teacher?
Mr. Frick

What is your favorite movie?
John Wick, John Wick: Chapter 2 and John Wick: Chapter 3 - Parabellum.

Who is your role model and why?
Shroud (Michael Grzesiek), famous twitch streamer and Counter-Strike: Global Offensive professional. He is known to have the best aim in the world and I want to be able to do what he does when it comes to streaming and competing.

What‚Äôs next after graduation?
I plan to attend esports tournaments.

#yoursalisbury

post_text:
A little Q&A with Salisbury Senior Collin Byrnes

What is your full name?
Collin Jackson Byrnes

What are your hobbies?
Football, disc golf

Do you have any pets?
Betty: a Saint Bernard

How would your friends describe you?
Kade Simo says I am glamorous.

What is your favorite subject?
History

Who is your favorite teacher and why?
Mr. Barna. His history classes have always kept me interested, and his electives are very fun to take.

What is your favorite Salisbury memory?
Beating Notre Dame

What is your favorite movie?
This Is the End

Are you involved in any community service projects?
I was involved in Camp Smile at Cedar Crest College with football, and I volunteered to work the snack stand at the SYA game with teammates.

Who is your role model and why?
Dwayne ‚ÄúThe Rock‚Äù Johnson because he is Dwayne ‚ÄúThe Rock‚Äù Johnson.

What‚Äôs next after graduation?
Still working on that, but I am continuing my education at Penn State University or West Chester University.

#yoursalisbury

Drawing, singing and making my own songs.

Funny, kind and caring.

Lifesmarts, because we learn a lot of important information we can use in life.

White Fang

Key Club

Who is your role model and why?
Mrs. Bruns, because she‚Äôs a hard worker and kind.

Hopefully a good paying job so I could travel to Canada.
